{
  "texts": [
    "Such methodologies can be applied to many different types of models and to variable levels of incompleteness.",
    "However, they are computationally demanding during construction of the database and inference optimization, and they exhibit sensitivity to noise.",
    "Learning-based methodsLearning-based methods construct a parameterized model towards learning a mapping between the two feature spaces of the complete and incomplete point cloud, typically using encoder-decoder NNs.",
    "For the shape representation, most models use voxels, which are intuitive and appropriate for 3D convolution.",
    "To maintain local geometric details, models are employed on direct point sets."
  ]
}